column5: Looking for a drive in out post.
These folks have a very good reputationemail [email protected]Just tell them ModernSportsman referred you
Not really Gogama though. (I'll be on Duncan the next two weeks )

I was in Gogama for a fishing tourney in June and stayed at Minnisinakwa Lodge it was clean,comfortable and had good firm beds.Also had indoor plumbing and an indoor shower.there is also a public sauna and a lounge.Didn't have time for either of those though.All in all I enjoyed my stay.
